V2.2.2: [V20202] by Calamath
- Added a keybind option for reverse cycle quest in response to a request to assign a different key.
- Added option to lock the position and size of the tracker panel.
- Added operation sounds to pinning, ignoring, sharing and picking out quests.
- Some minor QOL improvements for the gamepad quest journal options menu.
- Added the pick out quest keybind button to the gamepad quest journal options screen.

V2.2.1: [V20201] by Calamath
- Fixed an issue with quest sharing not working on the journal screen.

V2.2.0: [V20200] by Calamath
- Improved the vanilla quest journal to support CQuestTracker.
- You can now control whether to pin or ignore individual quests from the quest journal screen in both gamepad and keyboard mode.

V2.1.10: [V20110] by Calamath
- Initial adjustments to support ForceConsoleFlow.
- Updated API version to 101045 (ESO 10.3.x : Fallen Banners)

V2.1.9: [V20109] by Calamath
- Fixed UI errors on Update 45 PTS and guaranteed backward compatibility.

V2.1.8: [V20108] by Calamath
- Addressed an issue in gamepad mode where the Cycle Focused Quest press-key hold interaction and the target icon interaction assigned to the same hold-key would occur at the same time.
- Now we will cancel the CQuestTracker hold interaction when another action is assigned to the same hold key in gamepad mode. This does not affect keyboard mode.
- When a zone story is tracked and displayed in the tracker panel, a sound will now play when you switch the focus to the zone story. This is a rollout of recent improvements to the default quest tracker.
- Fixed an issue where the compact mode was not working as intended when you manually closed quest conditions in the tracker panel.
- Fixed a potential issue related to the tree open animation when you manually opening and closing the quest condition in the tracker panel.
- Updated API version to 101044 (ESO 10.2.x : Update 44)

V2.1.7: [V20107] by Calamath
- Added option to underline the focused quest name.
- Changed to hide the tracker panel when the player character dies.
- Some minor improvements to the quest tooltip, such as indicating the relevant DLC for the prologue quest.
- Updated API version to 101043 (ESO 10.1.x : Update 43)

